      <p>I struggled a lot with the website's structure. I wanted to create a website as light and clean as possible with the tools I learned, which are mainly Ruby on Rails.</p>
      <p>For that reason, I decided I didn't want to store data in databases so I wouldn't need any models. This is why my blog is written in the main blog view and each of my projects will have its own view file. The will to not store data also led me to discover that I can have a contact form without a model by using the <code>include ActiveModel::Model</code> functionalities along with some other modifications.</p>
