      <p>My next challenge was CSS. I learned the positioning concepts of floating and also about flexbox. I saw how important it is to write CSS that is as modular as possible so you can easily apply the same style in different parts of the website. I tried to use sizing that allows for the website to be as responsive and adaptable to smaller screens as possible. I read about the mobile-first approach but I decided to go desktop-first and adapt to mobile afterwards.</p>
      <p>Choosing the logo and colour palette also took me some time. I wanted a light website and some pastel colours but couldn't pick a favourite set! As for the logo, I drew 2 versions. The first was cute but seemed too childish so I went with the minimal one.</p>
